  "text": "A closer look at the MPI PSF shows that, while E T (x) and E N (x) are scalar fields, W T (x) and W N (x) are 2 nd order tensors. Hence h(x) is also 2 nd order tensor for each position x. It is important to note that h(x) (Eqn. 4) only depends on the tracer magnetic property H sat and the gradient field strength G, and is independent of scanning direction for adiabatic particle responses [CITATION_1] .",
